OHIO RIVER R. CO. v. SHANNON. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. May 5, 1903.) No. 461. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States for the Northern District of West Virginia. H. P. Camden, for plaintiff in error. V. B. Archer, for defendant in error.

Before GOFF, Circuit Judge, and BRAWLEY and BOYD, District Judges.

PER CURIAM.

We find no error in the judgment complained of. The same is affirmed.
